WSL-For-FreeBSD implements the Windows Subsystem for Linux (WSL2) protocol
for FreeBSD guests running in Hyper-V Generation 2 virtual machines.

This allows FreeBSD to be used as a WSL distribution alongside Linux distros,
providing:
- Terminal session support via hvbridge (PTY forwarding)
- Guest-to-host filesystem access via Plan9/9P2000.L (lib9p)
- Network configuration via GNS engine (NAT/Mirrored modes)
- DNS tunneling for Windows NRPT/VPN policy enforcement
- Interop server for CreateProcess, environment queries
- User tools: wslpath (path conversion), wslinfo (environment info)

The hvinit daemon runs as the init process, handling WSL protocol messages
over Hyper-V sockets (AF_HYPERV/hv_sock). The hvbridge process manages
terminal sessions via forkpty + PTY I/O relay.

